DESCRIPTION:THIS AGREEMENT PROVIDES FUNDING TO CITY OF WARWICK TO IMPLEMENT ITS PROJECT TO ACQUIRE AND INSTALL A SCADA SYSTEM AS DIRECTED IN THE 2022 CONSOLIDATED APPROPRIATIONS ACT.

THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS PROJECT IS TO UPGRADE THE EXISTING SCADA CONTROL AND TELEMETRY SYSTEMS AND DEVELOP A PLAN FOR SCADA CONTROL SYSTEM AND TELEMETRY IMPROVEMENTS AT THE WASTEWATER TREATMENT PLANT (WWTP) AND FORTY-NINE (49) LIFT STATIONS. ACTIVITIES:THE ACTIVITIES TO BE PERFORMED ARE:

1.  REPLACE THE EXISTING OBSOLETE RADIO SYSTEM;
2.  EVALUATE THE EFFECTIVENESS OF USING A REMOTE TELEMETRY UNIT VERSUS A PUMP STATION CONTROL SYSTEM; 
3.  ADDRESS CYBERSECURITY CONCERNS BY INCORPORATING RECOMMENDATIONS FROM THE CYBERSECURITY ASSESSMENT INTO THE SCADA UPGRADE; AND
4.  EVALUATE ALTERNATIVE METHODS OF OPERATOR INTERFACE AGAINST EXISTING OPERATOR TERMINALS CONSISTING OF INDUSTRIAL COMPUTERS WITH TOUCH SCREENS RUNNING IFIX SCADA SOFTWARE.SUBRECIPIENT:NO SUBAWARDS ARE INCLUDED IN THIS ASSISTANCE AGREEMENT.OUTCOMES:THE ANTICIPATED DELIVERABLE IS THE SUCCESSFUL UPGRADE TO THE SCADA SYSTEM HARDWARE, SOFTWARE, AND CONTROL PANELS FOR THE WARWICK WASTEWATER TREATMENT FACILITY.  REPLACING THE SCADA AND CONTROL SYSTEMS IS EXPECTED TO INCREASE THE EFFICIENCY OF PROCESS MONITORING AND OPERATOR CONTROL.  RELIABLE AND EFFICIENT COMMUNICATION AND CONTROLS BETWEEN ALL SYSTEM PROCESSES AND FACILITIES IS KEY TO OPERATING A COMPLIANT WASTEWATER TREATMENT FACILITY.
